DISCLAIMER: HARDWARE CONTROL WARNING

This software controls GPU hardware fan speeds. Improper use can cause:
- GPU overheating and potential hardware damage
- System instability or crashes
- Warranty void on affected hardware
- Data loss

SAFETY RECOMMENDATIONS:
- Always monitor GPU temperatures
- Never set fan speeds below 30% without continuous monitoring
- If GPU temperature exceeds 85Â°C, increase fan speed immediately
- Use automatic fan curve profiles for safest operation
- Reset to automatic control when not actively monitoring

